  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "An adaptation is a trait that has been shaped by [natural selection](./natural-selection.md) to perform a function that enhances the [organism](../../../terms/organism.md)'s fitness — its survival and reproductive success — in a particular environment. The term refers both to the trait itself and to the evolutionary process that produced it.",
